text: Wahoo (; from Dakota ; "arrow wood") is a city in Nebraska, United States. It is the county seat of Saunders County. In the 2020 census, 4,818 people lived there. ==History== Wahoo was built in 1870. The name of the town comes from the eastern wahoo (Euonymus atropurpureus). It is a shrub found on the banks of Wahoo Creek. The town was built by Czech, German, and Scandinavian settlers. Wahoo was the home of the John F. Kennedy College from 1965 until 1975.
